Responsibilities:
Plan, schedule, conduct and coordinate program of assigned Instrument calibration / troubleshooting work and projects either in Singapore or Overseas.
Analyze customer issues, process, reports, P&I drawings, tests and other data to plan service work for faster solution especially in wireless, Tank Gauging, Radar level instruments.
Ensure proper interdisciplinary coordination and effective communication on service projects / contracts and related activities.
Provide telephone technical support and recommendations to customers on instrument related issues and attend to Factory Acceptance Test for onshore and offshore customers.
Write professional reports and update companyâ€™s CRM system on the job progress.
Ensure all in-field activities are carried out safely complying with company Environmental Health & Safety (EHS) guidelines and procedures.
Requirements:
Degree/Diploma in Instrument/Electronics Engineering with 2 to 5 years of related experience in the instrumentation and controls field, particularly in Rosemount measuring instruments.
A team player with good problem solving skills and positive work attitude.
Able to travel on short notice.